                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/319: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-03T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 3, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Your 10, January 31, 3 p.m. Has the Greek Government altered its intention to
                    deport Insull? If not, will such expulsion take place prior to February 11th the
                    date on which his passport definitely expires? Keep Department fully informed of
                    developments particularly Insull’s destination if and when he is expelled.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
